[center][size=7][b]Just Give Up Man! (JGUM!)[/b][/size]
[size=5][b][color=#FFD700]🌟 BIG AI UPDATE (v2.0.0) 🌟[/color][/b][/size]
[b][color=#00ff00]STATUS: OFFICIAL RELEASE[/color][/b][/center]

[center][size=5][b]Important: JGUM now supports both Steam and PC Game Pass (Xbox Store) versions.[/b][/size]
[size=5][b]Full Turkish (TR) and English (EN) localization is supported.[/b][/size][/center]

[line]

[size=6][b]What Does This Mod Do?[/b][/size]

Just Give Up Man! (JGUM) makes surrender logic in Mount & Blade II: Bannerlord dynamic and realistic. No more grinding down every last starving defender; settlements now recognize hopeless situations and offer to surrender. Includes Field-lord and Patrol surrender logic with trait-based consequences.

[line]

[size=6][b]🚀 BIG AI UPDATE (v2.0.0) Features[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]🤖 AI vs AI Surrenders:[/b] Lords are no longer mindless drones! AI lords will now intelligently surrender to other AI lords if the odds are heavily against them in both field battles and sieges. Watch the living world react dynamically!
[*][b]🏳️ Voluntary Surrender:[/b] Tired of fighting a hopeless siege? Proactively offer a peaceful surrender of your settlement from the "Siege Strategies" menu. But watch out, rejecting peace hurts your Honor and Mercy!
[*][b]💰 Fief Purchase Offers:[/b] If defending against a leader with high Trade skill, they might offer you cold hard gold to peacefully hand over the keys without bloodshed.
[*][b]🗣️ 3rd Party Mod Integration (Rumour Has It):[/b] Built-in Interop API allows other mods (like [i]Rumour Has It[/i]) to instantly detect surrenders and generate tavern gossip about the cowardice or wisdom of lords!
[/list]

[line]

[size=6][b]Core Features[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Dynamic Settlement Surrender:[/b] Context-aware surrender offers during sieges based on starvation, wall health, and siege engines.
[*][b]Siege Negotiation:[/b] Proactive parley path with persuasion rounds and strategic consequences.
[*][b]Lord & Patrol Surrender:[/b] Outmatched enemies evaluate surrender based on strength ratios and personality traits (Valor, Calculating).
[*][b]Cross-Platform Support:[/b] Full compatibility with Steam and Xbox Store (PC Game Pass) folder structures.
[*][b]Localization:[/b] Full English and Turkish support included.
[/list]

[line]

[size=6][b]Configuration Modes[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]JSON Mode (Default):[/b] Works without any dependencies. Settings are read from [font=Courier New]config.json[/font].
[*][b]MCM Mode (Optional):[/b] If you have MCM installed, sliders appear automatically within the same [font=Courier New]JGUM[/font] module. No separate downloads required.
[/list]

[line]

[size=6][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[list=1]
[*]Download the latest package and extract it to your Bannerlord [font=Courier New]Modules[/font] folder.
[*]Enable [font=Courier New]JGUM[/font] in the launcher.
[*][b]Game Pass Users:[/b] If the mod doesn't load, go to [font=Courier New]Modules/JGUM/bin/Gaming.Desktop.x64_Shipping_Client[/font], right-click [font=Courier New]JGUM.dll[/font] -> Properties -> check [b]Unblock[/b].
[*][b]Load Order:[/b] Place JGUM after official modules and framework mods.
[/list]

[line]

[size=6][b]FAQ[/b][/size]

[b]Q: Is it compatible with Game Pass?[/b]
A: Yes! Version 1.0 includes dedicated support for the Xbox Store directory structure.

[b]Q: Do I need MCM?[/b]
A: No, it's optional. The mod works fine with default settings or manual JSON edits.

[b]Q: Is it safe mid-save?[/b]
A: Adding is safe. Removal is generally not recommended for any script-heavy mod; always keep a backup.

[line]

